This paper involves the use of an artificial neural network to analyze movement patterns and estimate blood alcohol content levels. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) sub-category, as well as the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Signal Processing (cs.SI) sub-categories. Additionally, the use of neural networks suggests that it could also belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the focus on designing effective prevention interventions suggests that it could also belong to the Cybersecurity (cs.CY) sub-category.
